<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - INSTALL - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place all three mainshaft sliding clutches in the neutral position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13027s3">Figure 283</hotlnk>). Install shifter housing gasket in position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13027s3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027s3" filename="../figg13/G13027S3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 283. Place Mainshaft Sliding Clutches in Neutral Position</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With all three shift yokes in the neutral position, install the shifter housing assembly on
                the case, fitting the shift yokes into the slots of the corresponding sliding clutches (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13027s4">Figure 284</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13027s4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027s4" filename="../figg13/G13027S4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 284. Install Shifter Housing Assembly on Case</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite 242 to the bolt threads. Install the 13 bolts in the housing and tighten to 35
                to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13027s5">Figure 285</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13027s5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13027s5" filename="../figg13/G13027S5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 285. Install and Tighten Bolts in Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>There are two sizes of bolts. The 1-1/2 inch bolts are used with lifting eyes.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
